RTRS - Leighton wins A $ 33 . 5 mln contract . Construction contractor Leighton Holdings Ltd ' s Thiess Contractors unit had won the last major roadworks contract for the Sydney Olympics 2000 site , the New South Wales ( NSW ) state government said on Thursday . NSW minister for the Olympics Michael Knight said in a statement the A $ 33 . 5 million contract includes the remaining roadworks , services and associated landscape works . Knight said preliminary design of the roads had begun and work is expected to start in April 1997 . At 2 . 15 p . m . ( 0315 GMT ) , Leighton shares were six cents higher at A $ 5 . 06 . - - Sydney newsroom 61 - 2 9373 - 1800 
